instructions: This set of rules can be used to predict the type of soybean disease present in a given data set. If the plant-growth is not equal to 0, the disease is 0 with 100% probability. If the stem is not equal to 1 the disease is 11 with 92% probability. When the int-discolor is equal to 2.0 the disease is 1 with 100% probability while when it is equal to 1.0 the disease is 4 with 100% probability. If the leaf-mild is equal to 1.0 then the disease is 5 with 100% probability and if it is equal to 2.0 the disease is 6 with 100% probability. The leafspot-size is a primary factor used to predict the disease, with 0.0 indicating diseases 8, 9, and 0.0, 1.0 indicating diseases 7, 10, 11, 14, 15, and 16 and 2.0 indicating disease 6.
